        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 6:58PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 658 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pleak, or near Rosenberg, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rosenberg, Richmond, Pecan Grove, Needville, Pleak, Fairchilds,
Beasley, Kendleton, and Cumings.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
